Direct Known Subclasses:
JavaPrintWriter, LispPrintWriter
public abstract class PrintWriter
extends java.io.PrintWriter

This class is similar to the java.io.PrintWriter class except it intelligently prints objects as well as simple types. It also abstracts some of the formatting features such that derived versions of this class can print various styles of formatting the objects.

For example, the LispPrintWriter class will print basic types and objects with a lisp like appearance. This is useful for the CommandLineSessionManager because it needs to present AreaPoolServer data in a lisp like format.

printUnknownObject

protected boolean printUnknownObject(java.lang.Object object)
This function tries to gain access to the attributes of the object using reflection, calls the get set methods, and prints out the values.

Since this function is used to print and for it's side effect of returning whether the printing was successful, care must be taken to ensure that this function doesn't do anything until it is sure that it can print something. NOTE: For speed, this function should probably cache the getMethods.

Parameters:
object - to reflect and print out values via get functions
Returns:
boolean indicating that at least one attribute was printed
